{"link_name": "Cisco BGP IPv4/IPv6 32-bit ASN", "type": "Template", "OS": "", "vendor": "Cisco", "minZabbVer": "3.0.x", "link_desc": "<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; padding-left: 2em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #24292e; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji'; font-size: 16px;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Auto-discovering</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.25em;\">Supports IPv6 BGP sessions</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.25em;\">Trigger for 80% prefix limit reached</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.25em;\">Monitoring of 32-bit ASNs supported</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.25em;\">Different message/severity based on ASN</li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0.25em;\">Trigger disabled when BGP in admin shutdown mode</li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #24292e; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji'; font-size: 16px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">This template uses the MIB cbgpPeer2Table, allowing identifying the ASN even when 32-bits. It also allows monitoring IPv6 sessions. The disadvantage of this MIB is that the cbgpPeer2RemoteAddr is an \"not-accessible\" object, this way, I had to obtain the IP addresses directly from the MIB index structure.</em></p>\n<h4 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; margin-top: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.25; color: #24292e; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji';\"><a id=\"user-content-zabbix-macros\" class=\"anchor\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; background-color: initial; color: #0366d6; float: left; padding-right: 4px; margin-left: -20p